<h2> About </h2>
<div class="about-section" style="max-width: 900px; margin: auto; padding: 20px; text-align: center; line-height: 1.6;">

    <p>
        This project is a web-based Network Intrusion Detection System (NIDS) that detects and classifies suspicious network activities using machine learning.
    </p>

    <p>
        It is built using HTML, CSS, JavaScript for the frontend, Node.js and Express for the backend, and MongoDB for data storage. The system analyzes network traffic to identify potential threats.
    </p>

    <h3>Features</h3>
    <p>
        Real-time intrusion detection • Attack classification • User-friendly interface • History tracking
    </p>

    <h3>Models Used</h3>
    <p>
        K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) • Random Forest • Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) • Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM)
    </p>

</div>
